Program: Outlook
Title: 02/07/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00trsk8
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 3 Jul 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the Colombian police sergeant who was held hostage by FARC rebels for nearly 13 years tells us how his friendship with a wild pig kept him sane. Also, the tragic effects of being a man who can feel no pain and in another instalment of our Edible City series a Spanish woman in London on the gazpacho that reminds her of her roots. Show less